Leave Policy


1. Purpose

This policy defines the types of leave available to employees and the process for availing them to ensure business continuity while supporting employee well-being.


2. Leave Entitlement

Casual Leave (CL): 12 days per calendar year
Sick Leave (SL): 18 days per calendar year

Leave entitlement is prorated for employees joining mid-year.


3. Leave Accrual

Leave accrual begins from the employeeâ€™s date of joining.
Unused casual leave lapses at the end of the calendar year.
Sick leave may be carried forward up to a maximum of 30 days (unless otherwise specified).


4. Leave Application Process

Casual leave must be applied at least 2 working days in advance through the HR system.
Sick leave should be informed to the reporting manager at the earliest possible time.
A medical certificate is mandatory for sick leave exceeding 2 consecutive working days.


5. Approval & Exceptions

All leave requests are subject to manager approval based on business requirements.
Misuse of leave may result in disciplinary action.
